meanings.definition: Misstamping: to stamp incorrectly or inaccurately.
meanings.sent1: She kept misstamping the letters on the envelope.
meanings.sent2: The worker misstamping the documents had to redo them.
meanings.sent3: The misstamping of the address made the letter go to the wrong house.
meanings.sent4: Her misstamping of the design turned the artwork into a mess.
meanings.sent5: The loud sound of misstamping echoed through the room.

meanings.definition: Misstamping: an instance of stamping something incorrectly.
meanings.sent1: The misstamping on the package caused confusion.
meanings.sent2: He noticed the misstamping on the coins at the museum.
meanings.sent3: The misstamping of the date made everyone laugh.
meanings.sent4: The misstamping on the ticket led to a mix-up at the event.
meanings.sent5: The misstamping was so obvious, it couldn't be ignored.

meanings.sent1: The misstamping label was removed from the product.
meanings.sent2: She pointed out the misstamping marks on the paper.
meanings.sent3: The misstamping error on the sign made it look funny.
meanings.sent4: The misstamping pattern on the fabric was unique.
meanings.sent5: The misstamping ink smudged, ruining the document.
